iliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMarc%20Cosentino%3C%2Fa%3E%20describes%20how%20his%20Harvard%20career%20led%20to%20writing%20%26quot%3BCase%20in%20Point.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E'Case%20in%20Point'%20is%20a%20bestselling%20resource%20for%20anyone%20interviewing%20for%20consulting%20jobs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20coached%20Harvard%20students%20through%20consulting%20interviews%2C%20focusing%20on%20confidence%20and%20communication.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20is%20an%20interview%20with%20Marc%20Cosentino%2C%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BCase%20in%20Point%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20has%20been%20the%20best-selling%20consulting%20case%20interview%20book%20worldwide%20for%20over%20two%20decades.%20This%20conversation%20has%20been%20condensed%20and%20edited%20for%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20started%20working%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fconsulting-career-options-alternatives-harvard-advisor-graduate-how-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EHarvard's%20Office%20of%20Career%20Services%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20late%201980s%2C%20I%20didn't%20expect%20to%20spend%20the%20next%2018%20years%20helping%20students%20break%20into%20consulting.%20I%20had%20just%20been%20laid%20off%20from%20my%20job%20at%20Fidelity%20Investments.%20A%20few%20months%20later%2C%20I%20found%20myself%20at%20Harvard%20College.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Harvard%2C%20I%20became%20the%20business%20counselor%20or%2C%20as%20the%20students%20liked%20to%20call%20me%2C%20%26quot%3BKeeper%20of%20the%20Dark%20Side.%26quot%3B%20About%20half%20the%20undergraduate%20class%20went%20through%20recruiting%20back%20then%2C%20mostly%20for%20consulting%20and%20investment%20banking%20jobs%2C%20and%20I%20was%20the%20one%20person%20who%20trained%20and%20coached%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20biggest%20insight%20from%20those%20years%20was%20that%20even%20the%20most%20brilliant%20students%20often%20lacked%20confidence.%20You'd%20think%20that%20people%20with%20their%20kind%20of%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20would%20brim%20with%20it%2C%20but%20they%20didn't.%20I%20probably%20spent%2090%25%20of%20my%20time%20building%20up%20their%20confidence.%20The%20second%20challenge%20was%20helping%20them%20think%20for%20themselves%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20critically%2C%20but%20independently.%20The%20third%20was%20communication.%20Even%20then%2C%20many%20students%20struggled%20to%20express%20ideas%20clearly%20and%20concisely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20I%20worked%20one-on-one%20with%20every%20student%20%E2%80%94%20coaching%2C%20running%20mock%20interviews%2C%20and%20helping%20them%20navigate%20recruiting.%20I%20taught%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fharvard-college-admissions-expert-how-to-get-into-ivy-league-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EHarvard%20College%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%201988%20to%201996%2C%20and%20it%20was%20during%20that%20time%20that%20I%20began%20writing%20guides%20to%20make%20the%20process%20easier.%20I%20wrote%20%26quot%3BThe%20Harvard%20College%20Guide%20to%20Investment%20Banking%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BThe%20Harvard%20College%20Guide%20to%20Consulting.%26quot%3B%20When%20you%20work%20for%20the%20Faculty%20of%20Arts%20and%20Sciences%2C%20though%2C%20anything%20you%20write%20belongs%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201997%2C%20I%20had%20an%20opportunity%20to%20switch%20over%20to%20Harvard's%20Kennedy%20School%20to%20become%20their%20%26quot%3BKeeper%20of%20the%20Dark%20Side.%26quot%3B%20I%20told%20them%20that%20I'd%20make%20the%20switch%2C%20but%20I%20also%20wanted%20to%20be%20able%20to%20write%20a%20book%20and%20own%20it.%20They%20let%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20there%20wasn't%20much%20out%20there%20on%20case%20interviews%2C%20even%20though%20consulting%20firms%20had%20been%20using%20them%20for%20decades.%20I%20had%20spent%20years%20sitting%20in%20on%20interviews%2C%20debriefing%20students%2C%20and%20talking%20to%20recruiters.%20I%20had%20all%20this%20insider%20knowledge%20%E2%80%94%20how%20interviews%20really%20worked%2C%20what%20students%20struggled%20with%2C%20and%20what%20firms%20looked%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20book%2C%20%26quot%3BCase%20in%20Point%2C%26quot%3B%20became%20a%20way%20to%20put%20it%20all%20in%20one%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wrote%20the%20first%20edition%20of%20%26quot%3BCase%20in%20Point%26quot%3B%20in%201999%20in%20just%20five%20weeks%2C%20working%20full%20time.%20It%20came%20out%20through%20a%20small%20educational%20publisher%2C%20but%20because%20they%20didn't%20include%20a%20barcode%2C%20it%20couldn't%20be%20sold%20in%20stores.%20I%20got%20the%20rights%20back%2C%20self-published%20the%20second%20edition%20in%202000%2C%20and%20never%20looked%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20it%20was%20%2420%20a%20book%2C%20so%20I%20was%20making%20a%20little%20under%20%2410%20for%20each%20copy%20sold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20remember%20walking%20down%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbookstores-become-centers-of-political-resistance-2017-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EHarvard%20Coop%20bookstore%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20a%20box%20of%20books%20and%20convincing%20them%20to%20take%2010%20copies%20on%20consignment.%20Two%20days%20later%2C%20they%20called%20and%20ordered%20100%20more.%20For%20the%20next%20three%20or%20four%20years%2C%20it%20was%20the%20Coop's%20best-selling%20nonfiction%20book.%20Within%20six%20months%2C%20I%20was%20making%20more%20money%20from%20book%20sales%20than%20from%20my%20Harvard%20salary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20tried%20marketing%20on%20Google%20for%20a%20little%20while%2C%20but%20it%20didn't%20work%20out%20well.%20It%20was%20all%20word%20of%20mouth.%20I%20was%20also%20traveling%20a%20lot%2C%20going%20to%20a%20lot%20of%20schools%20%E2%80%94%20that's%20how%20the%20book's%20reputation%20grew.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20been%20the%20bestselling%20case%20interview%20book%20in%20the%20world%20for%2025%20years%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20top%20consulting%20book%20on%20Amazon%20for%20about%20two%20decades.%20It%20even%20hit%20number%2037%20overall%20on%20Amazon%20when%20The%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20wrote%20about%20me%20in%202012.%20That%20happened%20to%20be%20the%20day%20Hurricane%20Sandy%20hit%20the%20East%20Coast.%20I%20like%20to%20think%20I%20could've%20cracked%20the%20top%2025%20if%20not%20for%20the%20storm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThroughout%20the%20years%2C%20%26quot%3BCase%20in%20Point%26quot%3B%20has%20sold%20around%20400%2C000%20copies%20in%20total.%20During%20its%20peak%20%E2%80%94%20between%202010%20and%202018%20%E2%80%94%20I%20sold%2025%2C000%20to%2030%2C000%20copies%20a%20year.%20These%20days%2C%20I%20sell%20closer%20to%2012%2C000.%20I%20still%20make%20about%20%2414%20to%20%2415%20in%20profit%20per%20copy%2C%20which%20allows%20me%20to%20live%20comfortably%20in%20Santa%20Barbara.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20updated%20the%20book%2012%20times%20because%20the%20field%20evolves.%20Each%20edition%20includes%20new%20cases%2C%20more%20data%20analysis%2C%20and%20new%20sections%20on%20topics%2C%20like%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%2C%20cover%20letters%2C%20and%20creativity.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcase-interview-consulting-firms-first-principles-thinking-2021-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ECase%20interviews%3C%2Fa%3E%20today%20are%20more%20sophisticated%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20not%20just%20profit%20and%20loss%20anymore.%20You%20might%20be%20asked%20to%20analyze%20a%20returns%20policy%20or%20a%20sustainability%20strategy.%20I%20like%20to%20say%20I%20craft%20cases%2C%20not%20just%20write%20them%2C%20because%20each%20one%20has%20a%20lesson%20built%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20still%20work%20with%20students%20and%20universities%2C%20and%20I%20hear%20constantly%20from%20readers%20who've%20used%20the%20book%20to%20land%20jobs%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmbb-leaders-consulting-firms-advising-leaders-and-ceos-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etop%20consulting%20