%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20what%20will%20open%20up%20the%20market%20to%20get%20companies%20like%20Mercedes%20and%20GM%20to%20buy%20lidars%20and%20put%20them%20in%20their%20vehicles.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2277c69ee2-4af2-4794-93bf-04630d9d8986%5C%22%3EThe%20problem%20with%20lidar%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwatch-live-self-driving-experts-discuss-the-future-with-bi-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eautomakers%20explore%20driverless%20functions%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Aguilar%20believes%20lidar%20will%20be%20an%20essential%20part%20of%20tomorrow's%20cars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELidar%20can%20be%20a%20little%20like%20a%20disco%20ball%3A%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ea%20laser%20is%20pointed%20at%20a%20mirror%20that%20is%20constantly%20moving%20on%20an%20electromagnetic%20motor%2C%20and%20the%20reflected%20light%20measures%20the%20distance%20of%20objects%20around%20whatever%20it's%20mounted%20on%2C%20such%20as%20an%20autonomous%20vehicle.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20achieve%20a%20better%20range%20with%20a%20lidar%2C%20you%20need%20a%20larger%20laser%20and%2C%20consequently%2C%20a%20larger%20mirror.%20That%20makes%20lidars%20more%20expensive%2C%20and%20when%20placed%20in%20a%20moving%20vehicle%2C%20the%20sensor%20could%20require%20constant%20adjustment.%20Companies%20have%20to%20%26quot%3Brecalibrate%20those%20sensors%2C%20redo%20alignment%2C%20or%20replace%20those%20sensors%2C%26quot%3B%20Aguilar%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAguilar%20said%20the%20problem%20with%20many%20lidar%20systems%20is%20how%20they're%20built.%20There%20can%20be%20numerous%20moving%20parts%20inside%20the%20sensor%2C%20which%20require%20frequent%20calibration%20and%20are%20susceptible%20to%20wear%20and%20tear%20when%20placed%20on%20top%20of%20a%20frequently%20moving%20car%2C%20the%20cofounder%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20talk%20to%20OEMs%20%E2%80%94%20Mercedes%2C%20Volvo%2C%20BMW%2C%20GM%20%E2%80%94%20they%20don't%20want%20lidar%20to%20have%20to%20be%20replaced%20every%20two%20or%20three%20months%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20that's%20what%20I%20was%20experiencing%20working%20at%20these%20companies%3A%20Every%20two%20to%20three%20months%2C%20something%20would%20break%20in%20this%20thing%20and%20we'd%20have%20to%20get%20them%20replaced.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20where%20silicon%20comes%20in.%20With%20silicon%2C%20Aguilar%20said%2C%20you're%20dealing%20with%20fewer%20and%20lighter%20moving%20parts%20that%20can%20last%20longer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESilicon%20is%20much%20more%20durable%2C%20the%20Omnitron%20CEO%20argues%2C%20and%20could%20handle%20the%20kinds%20of%20temperature%20fluctuations%20an%20autonomous%20vehicle%20would%20experience.%20Then%2C%20by%20using%20a%20chip%20manufacturing%20process%2C%20the%20parts%20are%20built%20with%20nanometer-level%20precision%20and%20can%20be%20built%20at%20scale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20you%20get%20a%20wafer%20with%20hundreds%20and%20thousands%20of%20these%20devices%20instead%20of%20building%20one%20at%20a%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Aguilar%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAround%20the%20time%20Aguilar%20was%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-layoff-moonshot-x-development-sergey-brin-larry-page-astro-2023-01%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGoogle's%20moonshot%20factory%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20single%20lidar%20unit%20could%20cost%20%24120%2C000.%20Today%2C%20a%20similar%20model%20could%20cost%20around%2010%20grand%20%E2%80%94%20a%20significant%20drop%2C%20in%20part%20thanks%20to%20better%20designs%20and%20increased%20manufacturing%20scale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAguilar%20says%20Omnitron's%20process%20brings%20down%20those%20same%20lidar%20units%20to%20%26quot%3Bthe%20hundreds%20of%20dollars.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2265a48352-1be7-4ad5-8d19-a6d983b9605f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20self-driving%20cars%20and%20robots%20need%20it%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20self-driving%20cars%2C%20Aguilar%20sees%20lidar%20as%20the%20key%20to%20covering%20rare%20edge%20cases%20on%20the%20roads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECameras%20are%20%26quot%3Bterrible%26quot%3B%20in%20low-light%20situations%2C%20he%20said.%20The%20cofounder%20used%20shadows%20as%20an%20example.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20a%20shadow%20is%20being%20cast%2C%20a%20car%20can%20get%20confused%20as%20to%3A%20Is%20that%20a%20real%20object%20or%20is%20that%20a%20shadow%3F%26quot%3B%20Aguilar%20said.%20That's%20where%20lidar%20comes%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Omnitron%20cofounder%20also%20sees%20humanoid%20robots%20as%20a%20ripe%20market%20for%20sensors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20like%20Agility%20Robotics%20use%20lidar%20to%20help%20their%20humanoid%20robots%20navigate%20their%20environments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20like%20humans%20rely%20on%20sensors%20beyond%20their%20eyes%20to%20determine%20the%20amount%20of%20force%20needed%20to%20pick%20up%20objects%2C%20Aguilar%20said%20robots%20will%20need%20lidar%20to%20understand%20the%20depth%20of%20their%20surroundings%20and%20the%20objects%20and%20people%20within%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAguilar's%20case%20for%20lidar%20in%20cars%20or%20robots%20echoes%20what%20many%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceos-on-autonomy-robotaxis-self-driving-nuro-kodiak-waabi-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ECEOs%20in%20the%20self-driving%20space%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20already%20said%20on%20the%20sensors%3A%20It%20all%20comes%20down%20to%20safety.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20bar%20for%20integrating%20(robots)%20into%20the%20human%20experience%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20going%20to%20be%20much%20higher%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20going%20to%20let%20this%20thing%20hold%20my%20baby%2C%20for%20example%2C%20if%20I%20don't%20know%20that%20this%20thing%20is%20robust%20and%20this%20sensor%20is%20really%2C%20really%20important%20for%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%