eativity%2C%20adaptability%2C%20and%20soft%20skills%20in%20AI%20career%20success.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EYoung%20AI%20talent%20is%20overthinking%20too%20many%20aspects%20of%20their%20careers%2C%20says%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworld-model-ai-explained-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGodmother%20of%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20do%20find%20many%20of%20the%20young%20people%20today%20think%20about%20every%20single%20aspect%20of%20an%20equation%20when%20they%20decide%20on%20jobs%20at%20some%20point%2C%26quot%3B%20Fei-Fei%20Li%20said%20on%20an%20episode%20of%20%26quot%3BLenny's%20Podcast%26quot%3B%20released%20on%20Sunday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELi%20is%20a%20longtime%20Stanford%20computer%20science%20professor%20famous%20for%20inventing%20ImageNet.%20Last%20year%2C%20she%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-startup-unicorns-with-tiny-teams-2025-5%23world-labs-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecofounded%20World%20Labs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20company%20building%20AI%20models%20to%20perceive%2C%20generate%2C%20and%20interact%20with%203D%20environments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20podcast%2C%20she%20said%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eit's%20a%20%26quot%3Bprivilege%26quot%3B%20to%20receive%20applications%20from%20young%20AI%20engineers%20and%20researchers%20who%20want%20to%20work%20at%20World%20Labs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20sometimes%20I%20do%20want%20to%20encourage%20young%20people%20to%20focus%20on%20what's%20important%20because%20I%20find%20myself%20constantly%20in%20mentoring%20mode%20when%20I%20talk%20to%20job%20candidates%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BNot%20necessarily%20recruiting%2C%20but%20just%20in%20mentoring%20mode.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20added%20that%20she%20sees%20young%20talent%20%26quot%3Boverfocusing%20on%20every%20minute%20decision%26quot%3B%20instead%20of%20asking%20themselves%20the%20most%20important%20questions%20like%3A%20%26quot%3BWhere's%20yo