0CR's%20campaigns%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcritical-role-campaign-four-matt-mercer-brennan-lee-mulligan-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elong-running%20Twitch%20stream%3C%2Fa%3E%20that's%20a%20mainstay%20of%20the%20company's%20sprawling%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECahill%20started%20watching%20the%20CR%20stream%20in%20October%202015%2C%20some%20eight%20months%20after%20the%20crew%20of%20eight%20had%20first%20started%20broadcasting%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcritical-role-campaign-four-matt-mercer-brennan-lee-mulligan-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BDungeons%20%26amp%3B%20Dragons%20campaign%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20several%20hours%20every%20Thursday%20night.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETen%20years%20on%2C%20the%20CR%20crew%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcritical-role-world-tour-australia-matthew-mercer-cofounders-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esells%20out%20arenas%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20has%20two%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-critical-role-8-cofounders-turned-game-amazon-hit-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAmazon-backed%20animated%20series%3C%2Fa%3E%20based%20on%20their%20%26quot%3BD%26amp%3BD%26quot%3B%20campaigns%2C%20and%20Cahill's%20gone%20from%20viewer%20to%20creative%20collaborator.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20just%20became%20one%20of%20those%20sources%20of%20light%20and%20hope%2C%26quot%3B%20Cahill%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20CR%20also%20became%2C%20at%20least%20for%20me%20personally%2C%20a%20place%20where%20we%20can%20escape%20to%20and%20feel%20some%20joy%20and%20win%20over%20bad%20guys.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20also%20drawn%20to%20CR%20as%20a%20property%20because%20it%20was%20his%20%26quot%3Bfavorite%20kind%20of%20storytelling%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20reminded%20him%20of%20the%20plot%20threads%20he'd%20tried%20to%20include%20in%20his%20own%20writing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20get%20the%20bitter%20and%20the%20sweet%2C%20we%20celebrate%20the%20things%20that%20are%20good%20and%20we%20mourn%20that%20which%20is%20bad%2C%20and%20we%20find%20a%20way%20to%20keep%20going%2C%26quot%3B%20Cahill%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2248a6b7cf-36c0-443d-9741-69d433dedbc4%5C%22%3EThe%20dream%20job%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20August%202023%2C%20he%20was%20approached%20by%20a%20contact%20working%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcritical-role-book-publishing-expansion-liam-obrien-cofounder-novels-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ECR's%20publishing%20arm%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20was%20looking%20to%20sign%20a%20writer%20that%20would%20be%20a%20good%20fit%20for%20%26quot%3BThe%20Armory%20of%20Heroes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECahill%20was%20given%20a%20brief%20to%20work%20with.%20However%2C%20he%20had%20the%20latitude%20to%20pitch%20ideas%20for%20how%20the%20book%20would%20flow%2C%20and%20he%20proposed%20a%20multi-character%20narrative%20that%20became%20the%20core%20of%20this%20CR%20encyclopedia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224650%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20page%20from%20'The%20Armory%20of%20Heroes.%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6919461789026fbb4d0dbe37%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Armory%20of%20Heroes%26quot%3B%20features%20character%20art%20and%20campaign%20lore%20from%20Critical%20Role.%3Cp%3EInsight%20Editions%2C%20art%20by%20Ana%20Fedina%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20comments%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcritical-roles-co-founders-talk-10th-anniversary-releases-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ECR%20co-founders%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20crew's%20lorekeeper%2C%20Dani%20Carr%2C%20and%20rounds%20of%20edits%2C%20his%20section%20of%20the%20book%20was%20done%2C%20pending%20illustrations%20from%20artist%20Ana%20Fedina.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20highlight%20for%20Cahill%20came%20when%20he%20received%20a%20note%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcritical-role-candela-obscura-liam-obrien-gothic-horror-gaming-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ECR%20cofounder%20Liam%20O'Brien%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20one%20section%20of%20the%20book%20dedicated%20to%20O'Brien's%20campaign%20character%2C%20Caleb%20Widogast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLiam%20had%20just%20written%20'perfection'%20next%20to%20it.%20I%20guess%20I%20captured%20some%20aspect%20of%20Caleb%20in%20a%20nutshell%2C%20and%20I%20think%20it%20was%20cool%20to%20see%20Liam%20had%20liked%20that%20and%20appreciated%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Cahill%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECahill%20said%20working%20with%20CR%20also%20meant%20he%20had%20to%20keep%20a%20clear%20separation%20between%20being%20a%20fan%20and%20a%20professional.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20both%20very%20business%20as%20usual%20and%20also%20very%2C%20very%20amazing%20when%20you%20have%20those%20moments%20of%20connecting%20with%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20business%20as%20much%20as%20it%20is%20art%2C%20and%20I%20think%20part%20of%20the%20process%20is%20being%20able%20to%20say%3A%20'Hey%2C%20I'm%20a%20huge%20fan.%20Now%2C%20what%20do%20you%20want%20me%20to%20do%20with%20page%20three%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225714494e-453e-49c4-b4ec-1ff9d5708187%5C%22%3EGetting%20your%20work%20in%20front%20of%20the%20right%20people%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECahill%20has%20worked%20on%20and%20published%20a%20hefty%20stack%20of%20science%20fiction%20and%20fantasy%20works%20outside%20his%20work%20for%20Critical%20Role.%20This%20summer%2C%20he%20published%20his%20debut%20fantasy%20novel%2C%20%26quot%3BAudition%20for%20the%20Fox.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECahill%20said%20there%20isn't%20a%20one-size-fits-all%20approach%20to%20getting%20a%20cool%20gig%20in%20the%20creative%20industries%2C%20but%20there%20are%20things%20you%20can%20do%20to%20get%20your%20work%20in%20front%20of%20decision-makers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20it%20starts%20with%20being%20vocal%20about%20what%20you%20want%20to%20do%20and%20broadening%20your%20network%2C%20while%20not%20being%20pushy%20about%20securing%20opportunities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20way%20to%20do%20it%20that%20is%20not%20like%20'Hey%20man%2C%20introduce%20me%20to%20your%20cool%20friend%2C%20or%20we're%20not%20friends.'%20There%20are%20ways%20to%20use%20your%20network%20of%20friends%20and%20creators%20and%20be%20open%20to%20helping%20people%20right%20back%2C%26quot%3B%20Cahill%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20in%20the%20publishing%20industry%2C%20being%20OK%20at%20becoming%20comfortable%20with%20asking%20people%20to%20introduce%20you%20could%20lead%20to%20great%20opportunities%2C%20and%20conversations%20about%20what%20you're%20interested%20in%20doing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETip%20two%20about%20networking%20your%20way%20into%20jobs%2C%20Cahill%20said%2C%20is%20to%20pay%20it%20forward%20when%20you%20have%20an%20opportunity%20that%20may%20suit%20someone%2C%20and%20view%20it%20as%20helping%20a%20friend%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20see%20any%20point%20in%20being%20an%20obstacle%20to%20people%2C%20or%20'being%20better'%20than%20anybody%2C%26quot%3B%20Cahill%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20all%20in%20here%20to%20help%20each%20other.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECahill's%20final%20tip%20for%20writers%20seeking%20success%20in%20publishing%20is%20that%20%26quot%3Bpersistence%20is%20key%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20face%20of%20rejection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20an%20industry%20that%20does%20not%20love%20you%20back.%20It's%20also%20an%20industry%20that%20does%20not%20reward%20sitting%20on%20one's%20laurels%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20is%20a%20big%20fan%20of%20the%20follow-up%20email%20and%20check-ins%20after%20two%20weeks.%20However%2C%20it's%20also%20important%20to%20be%20mindful%20of%20a%20potential%20collaborator's%20time%